<br>
All things considered, it's not very often that you see this anymore especially under the circumstances described in the original post. The problem with it was nailed by Absolute Master in subsequent posts which is that if they do it manaless it really does take an insane amount of time. Bards getting their mana back takes FOREVER. If they use mana to do it and they charm swarm then it gets done pretty darn fast. However, they won't be doing that again for like 4 hours (or something equally ridiculous. I don't remember their mana recovery time exactly. It's for-freaking-ever though).<br>
<br>
Moreover, while on the odd occasion you see it there might be a pang of jealousy there is nothing to get worked up over here. In fact, bards can solo stuff WAY faster, more efficiently, and with less risk than swarm kiting. If you take a look at the most powerful and skilled bards around you'll find they aren't doing this that often. When they do I'll wager it's mainly for a laugh or done out of boredom.<br>
<br>
At first blush, this may seem very unfair and &quot;unbalanced&quot; but again I think it's rare. If this were happening with the frequency of quadding then you might have a point. Until then, this wizard won't worry about it.<br>
<br>
