And the charm cap is 51, so if you want to use it to level past 60 its' not very effective.<br>
<br>
Well they can nerf away all they want, IMO Bards are pretty weak already but I play them because they are the most fun class to play for me.<br>
<br>
It's not hard to &quot;twist 4 songs&quot;, and it's not harder to &quot;twist 4 songs and melee&quot;.<br>
<br>
To twist 4 songs, clicking off and on a song every 3 seconds, switching instruments at the same time, running backwrds, strafing right, perhaps target your self, stop songs and right click an invis item to break charm, perhaps push &quot;tab&quot; to target, start new song, all this in ten seconds, and remember you are not standing still, you are running with selos speed, is perhaps a little bit &quot;harder&quot; at least it takes some speed. <br>
<br>
Almost every Bard who do this, do it in a different way. Personally I both twist and move with my left hand normally, so I can use the mouse all the time doing the other things needed to be done.<br>
It's usually called the &quot;shot em' up setup&quot;, but I think the more common one is the &quot;both hands on keyboard&quot; setup. Some use both, I actually use the &quot;both hands on keyboard&quot; setup sometimes too.<br>
I'm not the one to say if it's hard enough to make people happy.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now the problem is, as I see it, if VI continues to &quot;nerf&quot; everything, all we Bards have to do is standing there meleeing and twisting, a Wizard will stand, push DD spell, sit, stand push DD and so on. <br>
<br>
You know, I'm not just standing there doing &quot;nothing&quot; when I group, that's not my idea of having fun really, I want to use the abilities we have.<br>
Some people may be happy playing Bards/Wizards like the example above, some is not. <br>
<br>
You can argue Bard kiting is overpowered, you can argue that Rogues and Wizards are overpowered when raiding, it will lead nowhere.<br>
<br>
Also every class that can charm &quot;can&quot; charm kite too, it's not about running speed, a lot of Bards use SoW potions or Jboots to kite.<br>
<br>
I guess VI new &quot;vision&quot; about Bards is we should be a second class Enchanetr, so some of them whine about that, and of course they have the right to do so if they feel hurt. Others complain we &quot;can&quot; charm kite for 10 minutes, others complain we have dots and so on. <br>
<br>
<br>
As long as we can cast while running, and are(now days) one of the fastest classes, I will probably continue to play, time will tell.<br>
